"{\"uid\": \"heraldextra.com-top-headlines-2024-jul-18-paris-police-are-sealing-off-the-seine-river-ahead-of-the-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"A police officer checks people at the security perimeter set up for the Olympic Games, outside Notre Dame cathedral, Thursday, July 18, 2024 in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A police officer\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 16}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 24, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"the security perimeter\", \"from\": 34, \"to\": 56}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 68, \"to\": 85}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre Dame cathedral\", \"from\": 95, \"to\": 115}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Starting Thursday, parts of the French capital will only be accessible to people who have registered for a QR code, as part of the massive security operation ahead of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9726035708849449, \"rank\": 0.024862298408496856, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 168}, {\"ngram\": \"parts\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 175}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 231}, {\"ngram\": \"a QR code\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 274}, {\"ngram\": \"the massive security operation\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 308}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 346}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(AP Photo/David Goldman) PARIS (AP) - A special kind of iron curtain came down across central Paris on Thursday, with the beginning of an Olympic anti-terrorism perimeter along the banks of the River Seine sealing off a kilometers-long (miles-long) area to Parisians and tourists who had not applied in advance for a pass.\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999298884201, \"rank\": 6.958925886480203e-08, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\", \"score\": 0.9999999671094889, \"rank\": 3.288636285846428e-08, \"text\": \"David Goldman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\"}, {\"begin\": 381, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999298884201, \"rank\": 6.958925886480203e-08, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 443, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A special kind\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"iron curtain\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"the beginning\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic anti-terrorism perimeter\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"a kilometers-long (miles-long) area\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"advance\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"a pass\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The words on many lips were \\\"QR code,\\\" the pass that grants access beyond snaking metal barriers that delineate the security zone set up to protect the Olympic Games' opening ceremony on July 26.\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The words\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"many lips\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"QR code\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"the pass\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 739}, {\"ngram\": \"snaking metal barriers\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"the security zone\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games' opening ceremony\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 856}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not know it started today,\\\" said Emmanuelle Witt, a 35-year-old communications freelancer who was stopped by police near the Alma bridge while biking across town.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuelle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.92180172983031e-20, \"text\": \"Emmanuelle\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuelle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuelle\"}, {\"begin\": 921, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ernst_Witt\", \"score\": 0.9820249533128121, \"rank\": 0.016154657565599893, \"text\": \"Witt\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ernst_Witt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ernst_Witt\"}, {\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alma_Mahler\", \"score\": 0.9965254457994261, \"rank\": 0.0028225612154812005, \"text\": \"Alma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alma_Mahler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alma_Mahler\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 35-year-old communications freelancer\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 992}, {\"ngram\": \"town\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She desperately went on her phone to fill out the online form to get her QR code, unaware that the vetting process could take several days.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her phone\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"the online form\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"her QR code\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"the vetting process\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"several days\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those with the precious code - either on their phones or printed out on pieces of paper - passed smoothly past police checkpoints at gaps in the barriers taller than most people.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the precious code\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"their phones\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"pieces\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"paper\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"police checkpoints\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"gaps\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"the barriers\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those without got mostly turned away - with no amount of grumbling and cajoling making officers budge.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no amount\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1414}, {\"ngram\": \"officers\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's too much, that's over the top, that whole thing is a pain,\\\" grumbled Nassim Bennamou, a delivery man who was denied access to the street leading to Notre Dame Cathedral on his scooter.\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1657, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"that whole thing\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"a pain\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"Nassim Bennamou\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"a delivery man\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1573}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"the street\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre Dame Cathedral\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"his scooter\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Even the GPS is confused, I have no idea how I am going to work today,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even the GPS\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1672}, {\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While authorities announced the code system last year and have been meeting with local residents for months to explain the restrictions, not everyone was aware.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"the code system\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"local residents\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"months\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"the restrictions\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"not everyone\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officers patiently explained to visitors without the pass how to reach iconic Paris monuments without going through the restricted zone.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1982, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Officers\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1912}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"the pass\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"the restricted zone\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had no idea we needed a QR code,\\\" said Takao Sakamoto, 55, who was denied access to the Eiffel Tower near the Bir Hakeim Metro station.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Takao_Sakamoto\", \"score\": 0.9999998026910556, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Takao Sakamoto\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Takao_Sakamoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Takao_Sakamoto\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"a QR code\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bir Hakeim Metro station\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Visiting from Japan with his wife, he took a photo of the tower from a distance, behind fences and police cars.\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Japan\", \"score\": 0.998846607744807, \"rank\": 0.0011546066753215535, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his wife\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"a photo\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"a distance\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"fences\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2276}, {\"ngram\": \"police cars\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That will do,\\\" Sakamoto remarked with despair.\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sakamoto\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"despair\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other hand, visitors who were lucky enough to come across officers who leniently let them pass without QR codes and others who'd equipped themselves with them were treated to the sight of near-empty riverside boulevards that, in normal times, heave with traffic.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"officers\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"QR codes\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2472}, {\"ngram\": \"the sight\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"near-empty riverside boulevards\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"normal times\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no one around!\\\"\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"sang a happy cyclist on a street he had largely to himself.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a happy cyclist\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2660}, {\"ngram\": \"a street\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2672}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With police seemingly everywhere, another man walking past a riverside caf\\u00e9 with fewer than usual customers loudly quipped: \\\"You can leave your money and cell phones on the tables, there is definitely no thieves!\\\"\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2913, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"another man\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2745}, {\"ngram\": \"a riverside caf\\u00e9\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"fewer than usual customers\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"your money and cell phones\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2865}, {\"ngram\": \"the tables\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"no thieves\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's surreal, it really feels like we are the only ones here,\\\" said Sarah Bartnicka from Canada.\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2984, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Platt\", \"score\": 0.9914065417045183, \"rank\": 0.00866772127153744, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Platt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Platt\"}, {\"begin\": 3005, \"end\": 3011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999996830411, \"rank\": 3.1576738713412533e-10, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only ones\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enjoying a morning jog with a friend, the 29-year-old took a selfie with a police officer on the deserted I\\u00e9na bridge to capture the moment.\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3153, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a morning jog\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"a friend\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3049}, {\"ngram\": \"a selfie\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3080}, {\"ngram\": \"a police officer\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3102}, {\"ngram\": \"the deserted I\\u00e9na bridge\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3130}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has repeatedly suffered deadly extremist attacks, most notably in 2015.\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3155, \"end\": 3160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"deadly extremist attacks\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up to 45,000 police and gendarmes as well as 10,000 soldiers are being deployed for Olympic security.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3334, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Up to 45,000 police\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3252}, {\"ngram\": \"gendarmes\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"as well as 10,000 soldiers\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3293}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic security\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I understand why they are doing this,\\\" said Carla Money, a 64-year-old American who managed to pass the barriers with her family.\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3381, \"end\": 3386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carla_Tortelli\", \"score\": 0.9569109171717545, \"rank\": 0.0450285603040126, \"text\": \"Carla\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carla_Tortelli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carla_Tortelli\"}, {\"begin\": 3408, \"end\": 3416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992323865, \"rank\": 5.256999342137198e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the barriers\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3449}, {\"ngram\": \"her family\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some business owners inside the security zone grumbled that sharply reduced foot-fall would hurt their bottom line.\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3583, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some business owners\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3488}, {\"ngram\": \"the security zone\", \"from\": 3496, \"to\": 3513}, {\"ngram\": \"sharply reduced foot-fall\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3553}, {\"ngram\": \"their bottom line\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have locked me up like a prisoner,\\\" said Raymond Pignol.\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Asquith\", \"score\": 0.9999664336000256, \"rank\": 3.3567526762589866e-05, \"text\": \"Raymond\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Asquith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Asquith\"}, {\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Pignol\", \"score\": 0.9101295171701695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pignol\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Pignol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Pignol\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a prisoner\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His restaurant, L'Auberge Caf\\u00e9, near the Pont Neuf that spans the Seine, is just inside the metal fencing.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3714, \"end\": 3719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3942748207102674e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His restaurant\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3662}, {\"ngram\": \"L'Auberge Caf\\u00e9\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3678}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont Neuf\", \"from\": 3685, \"to\": 3698}, {\"ngram\": \"the metal fencing\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The perimeter went into effect early Thursday morning and will last through the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The perimeter\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3769}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 3780, \"to\": 3786}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As an exception, Paris has decided to hold the opening of its first Games in a century on the river rather than in a stadium, like previous host cities.\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3863, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an exception\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 3861}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening\", \"from\": 3889, \"to\": 3900}, {\"ngram\": \"its first Games\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 3919}, {\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 3932}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 3936, \"to\": 3945}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 3961, \"to\": 3970}, {\"ngram\": \"previous host cities\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 3997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the river security measures will be lifted after the show.\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the river security measures\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officers were under instructions to be polite and patient as employees on their way to work and others dealt with the perimeter and the passes for the first time.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Officers\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4075}, {\"ngram\": \"instructions\", \"from\": 4087, \"to\": 4099}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4137}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4150}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 4163, \"to\": 4169}, {\"ngram\": \"the perimeter\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4194}, {\"ngram\": \"the passes\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4209}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris police chief Laurent Nunez said that after the initial 24 hours of being accommodating, officers would apply the rules much more firmly, with no more looking the other way for those without QR codes.\", \"from\": 4230, \"to\": 4439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4234, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.468348329671634e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the initial 24 hours\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4303}, {\"ngram\": \"officers\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4336}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4358}, {\"ngram\": \"QR codes\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Ogden Newspapers of 